Endesa to Invest $105 Million in Peru Generator, Comercio Says

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-09-09T13:42:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/endesa-to-invest-105-million-in-peru-generator-comercio-says.html
Endesa SA (ELE)  plans to invest $105
million to expand one of its Peruvian units amid rising power
demand,  El Comercio  said, citing Chairman Borja Prado Eulate.  Endesa plans to upgrade its north coastal electricity
generator  Empresa Electrica de Piura SA (ELPIUBC1) , the Lima-based
newspaper reported. Prado met President Ollanta Humala in  Lima 
yesterday, El Comercio said.  Endesa will also add power lines and substations at its
Edelnor SA electricity distributor in Lima, El Comercio said.
Endesa has spent $310 million on its Peruvian units including
generator Edegel SA in the past five years, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
